ed? I could use user classes instead. Also, I wonder if the commonSuperClass target test classes are included, especially since the previous setup had JDK. I'm considering switching to custom helper classes to ensure the agent records and coverage marks are on point. I need to check if Class.forName can load nested private classes!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing class naming and loading**\\n\\nI'm examining how the binary name works with inner classes. If an internal leftType has a $, getCommonSuperClass will replace slashes with dots, keeping names like cglib.cglib_nodep.ClassWriterTest$First intact. I wonder if Class.forName can load private nested classes by name, which should cover reflection queries. However, I need to consider metadata for private nested classes with the agent generating it. Since there aren't running tests, that’s okay. \\n\\nThere’s a rule against $ in test class names, but inner test helper class names still generate class files with $. Alternatively, I could use top-level package-private helper classes in the same file without the $. For example, I could have a structure like abstract class ClassWriterTestBaseList extending AbstractList<String> and a final ClassWriterTestArrayList extending it. It’s crucial to remember that additional top-level class names can be considered \\\"test classes,\\\" and all must be public, even though these helpers aren’t test classes. Furthermore, a Java file can only contain one public class.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating class accessibility and design**\\n\\nI need to remember not to use a $ in the Class.forName string for top-level helpers. That's good, but if my user-code-filter includes packages, that could be tricky.\\n\\nTo find a common super, I've decided that ClassWriterSiblingOne and ClassWriterSiblingTwo should extend ClassWriterTestBase. When getCommonSuperClass loads both and climbs, it should return cglib/cglib_nodep/ClassWriterTestBase. I’m wondering if I need it to be abstract; maybe I should just implement it directly. \\n\\nI could also consider a setup that’s both direct and natural, particularly with top-level user classes triggering various cases. For safety, I want to avoid reflection and rely on public APIs or protected extension points, which should be acceptable. \\n\\nNow, I’m thinking about whether a dynamic-access class should have its own dedicated Java test file. Adding top-level helper classes may be okay, but public static nested classes could avoid some of those complexities. However, a $ target might seem odd – top-level classes seem better. \\n\\nI do need to consider Class.forName on package-private classes outside their library being loaded by a library class in another package. Since Class.forName can load non-public classes too, using isAssignableFrom should be fine. I’ll adjust the ClassWriterTest to ensure package-private top-level classes follow the public ones and use leftType = ClassWriterFirstSibling.class.getName().replace('.', '/') for clarity.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_j2r5kBFDaPI5tiNGs05NXnA9|fc_0d0c9d55cadd33ef0169fb86ae106481a3a127ed862efe4938", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/src/test/java/cglib/cglib_nodep/ClassWriterTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage cglib.cglib_nodep;\n\nimport net.sf.cglib.asm.ClassWriter;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class ClassWriterTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void resolvesCommonSuperclassForApplicationClasses() {\n        ExposingClassWriter writer = new ExposingClassWriter();\n\n        String commonSuperClass = writer.commonSuperClass(\n                internalName(ClassWriterFirstSibling.class),\n                internalName(ClassWriterSecondSibling.class));\n\n        assertThat(commonSuperClass).isEqualTo(internalName(ClassWriterBaseSibling.class));\n    }\n\n    private static String internalName(Class<?> type) {\n        return type.getName().replace('.', '/');\n    }\n\n    private static final class ExposingClassWriter extends ClassWriter {\n        private ExposingClassWriter() {\n            super(0);\n        }\n\n        private String commonSuperClass(String leftType, String rightType) {\n            return super.getCommonSuperClass(leftType, rightType);\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nclass ClassWriterBaseSibling {\n}\n\nfinal class ClassWriterFirstSibling extends ClassWriterBaseSibling {\n}\n\nfinal class ClassWriterSecondSibling extends ClassWriterBaseSibling {\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 661, "output": 904, "cacheRead": 28160, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29725, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778091671727, "responseId": "resp_0d0c9d55cadd33ef0169fb86998a9081a3a693c97bbf03e486"}}
