ameMergeSample\", null,\n                \"java/lang/Object\", null);\n        writeConstructor(writer);\n        writeBranchingFactory(writer);\n        writer.visitEnd();\n\n        byte[] classFile = writer.toByteArray();\n\n        assertThat(classFile).isNotEmpty();\n    }\n\n    private static void writeConstructor(ClassWriter writer) {\n        MethodVisitor constructor = writer.visitMethod(ACC_PUBLIC, \"<init>\", \"()V\", null, null);\n        constructor.visitCode();\n        constructor.visitVarInsn(ALOAD, 0);\n        constructor.visitMethodInsn(INVOKESPECIAL, \"java/lang/Object\", \"<init>\", \"()V\");\n        constructor.visitInsn(RETURN);\n        constructor.visitMaxs(0, 0);\n        constructor.visitEnd();\n    }\n\n    private static void writeBranchingFactory(ClassWriter writer) {\n        MethodVisitor method = writer.visitMethod(ACC_PUBLIC | ACC_STATIC, \"create\",\n                \"(Z)L\" + internalName(ClassWriterBaseSibling.class) + \";\", null, null);\n        Label createSecondSibling = new Label();\n        Label returnSibling = new Label();\n\n        method.visitCode();\n        method.visitVarInsn(ILOAD, 0);\n        method.visitJumpInsn(IFEQ, createSecondSibling);\n        method.visitTypeInsn(NEW, internalName(ClassWriterFirstSibling.class));\n        method.visitInsn(DUP);\n        method.visitMethodInsn(INVOKESPECIAL, internalName(ClassWriterFirstSibling.class), \"<init>\", \"()V\");\n        method.visitJumpInsn(GOTO, returnSibling);\n        method.visitLabel(createSecondSibling);\n        method.visitTypeInsn(NEW, internalName(ClassWriterSecondSibling.class));\n        method.visitInsn(DUP);\n        method.visitMethodInsn(INVOKESPECIAL, internalName(ClassWriterSecondSibling.class), \"<init>\", \"()V\");\n        method.visitLabel(returnSibling);\n        method.visitInsn(ARETURN);\n        method.visitMaxs(0, 0);\n        method.visitEnd();\n    }\n\n    private static String internalName(Class<?> type) {\n        return type.getName().replace('.', '/');\n    }\n\n    private static final class ExposingClassWriter extends ClassWriter {\n        private ExposingClassWriter() {\n            super(0);\n        }\n\n        private String commonSuperClass(String leftType, String rightType) {\n            return super.getCommonSuperClass(leftType, rightType);\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nclass ClassWriterBaseSibling {\n}\n\nfinal class ClassWriterFirstSibling extends ClassWriterBaseSibling {\n}\n\nfinal class ClassWriterSecondSibling extends ClassWriterBaseSibling {\n}\n"}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Clarifying test class rules**\n\nI'm thinking about the guidelines on using top-level test classes and their public status, especially considering the new rules. It seems like we shouldn’t use reflection directly, but the ClassWriter API does that naturally with Class.forName. I need to explore adding tests with ClassWriter's public API while focusing on the call site. There are concerns about whether my direct calls will be considered non-public, especially if the agent doesn't generate the metadata during runtime. I'll need to balance direct versus dynamic access in the tests.\n\n**Exploring Native Image testing**\n\nI'm considering the possibility that my Native Image test might pass after the metadata merge. However, if the metadata isn't generated from the direct call, it complicates things. It sounds like I could use ClassWriter's COMPUTE_FRAMES with custom application classes to mark the calls. The idea is to add a natural API to enhance coverage, especially for dynamic coverage. I think implementing both direct and natural tests is key for better coverage while ensuring I utilize the public ClassWriter to trigger the call site effectively. I'll also need to import the necessary components for this.\n\n**Defining class construction**\n\nI'm diving into using internal class names from the helper, considering the method signature as \"(Z)L...;\". It looks like I need a constructor for the generated class to return the branch correctly. Given that First and Second classes have implicit package-private no-arg constructors, I realize the generated class isn’t loaded, just a byte array is created. However, the MethodWriter doesn’t check for existing constructors. The stack map compute still needs to align with class file version V1_6. I’m thinking about generating the class with the method choose(boolean) and possibly omitting the constructor, though addi